result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both Cause Injury/Operate While und.Influence (1st) (PAC<0.15) [Modifiers: Repeater] and Cause Injury while Operating with PAC (1st) (PAC<0.15) [Modifiers: Repeater]. The defendant was found guilty of Cause Injury/Operate While und.Influence (1st) (PAC<0.15) [Modifiers: Repeater] and the other charge, Cause Injury while Operating with PAC (1st) (PAC<0.15) [Modifiers: Repeater] was dismissed by the court.

  • Justin Lee Bredvick was found guilty of Hit and Run-Involve Injury [Modifiers: Repeater], an unclassified felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.67(1).
  • Justin Lee Bredvick was found guilty of Cause Injury/Operate While und.Influence (1st) (PAC<0.15) [Modifiers: Repeater], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(2)(a)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.
